1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,158
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,108 --> 00:00:11,182
First, you do a warm-up: Staff will name letters from the your name or a familiar word.

3
00:00:11,182 --> 00:00:13,953
You point first, then presses.

4
00:00:13,953 --> 00:00:18,505
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

5
00:00:18,505 --> 00:00:25,394
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Use simple words such as cat, bus and tea.

6
00:00:25,394 --> 00:00:29,334
After each word, press Space before the next word.

7
00:00:29,334 --> 00:00:34,755
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type the word: cat.

8
00:00:34,755 --> 00:00:41,358
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Practise holding Shift and pressing one letter.

9
00:00:41,358 --> 00:00:44,548
Keep this calm; it is a stretch task.

10
00:00:44,548 --> 00:00:47,061
Take one activity at a time.

11
00:00:47,061 --> 00:00:51,603
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

